  "datePublished": "2026-03-01",
  "description": "¶What this lesson covers What web accessibility means, why it matters, the standards that guide it, and the design principles that make web content usable by people across the full range of human ability and circumstance.\n¶Prerequisites Document Structure and Semantic HTML.\n¶What accessibility means Web accessibility means that people with disabilities can perceive, understand, navigate, and interact with web content. The term covers a wide range of conditions — visual, auditory, motor, cognitive, neurological — and an equally wide range of assistive technologies: screen readers, magnifiers, voice control, switch devices, eye trackers, Braille displays.\n",
